            <h1><b class="syntax_textcolor">1) C# Math</b></h1>
            <p><b class="syntax_textcolor">C# Math</b> class has many methods that allows you to perform mathematical tasks on numbers.</p><br /><hr />
        

            <h1><b class="syntax_textcolor">2) C# Math Types</b></h1>
        <ul>
            <li><b class="syntax_textcolor">Math.Max() - </b>method can be used to find the highest value of x and y.</li>
            <li><b class="syntax_textcolor">Math.Min() - </b>method can be used to find the lowest value of of x and y.</li>
            <li><b class="syntax_textcolor">Math.Sqrt() - </b>method returns the square root of x.</li>
            <li><b class="syntax_textcolor">Math.Abs(x) - </b>method returns the absolute (positive) value of x.</li>
            <li><b class="syntax_textcolor">Math.Round() - </b>rounds a number to the nearest whole number.</li>
        </ul><br /><hr />



          <h1><b class="syntax_textcolor">3) C# Math Types Examples : </b></h1>
          <pre style="font-size:20px">

             <b class="syntax_textcolor">             
             Console.WriteLine(Math.Max(5, 10));    // output -- 10
             Console.WriteLine(Math.Min(5, 10));    // output -- 5
             Console.WriteLine(Math.Sqrt(64));      // output -- 8
             Console.WriteLine(Math.Abs(-4.7));     // output -- 4.7
             Console.WriteLine(Math.Round(9.99));   // output -- 10
             </b>
         </pre>
